headlines.description: — Already a No. 1 in his brief NBA career, Paolo Banchero is now a notable No. 2 for Orlando.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero's career-high 42 not enough as Magic lose to Cavs, who get 35 from Donovan Mitchell

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 32 of his career-high 49 points in the second half and the Memphis Grizzles handed the Detroit Pistons their 18th straight loss, 116-102 on Wednesday night
headlines.shortLinkText: Desmond Bane scores career-high 49 points, Grizzlies send Pistons to 18th straight loss

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored a season-high 50 points and had 13 rebounds to help the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Washington Wizards 131-126 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores season-high 50 points, 76ers beat Wizards 131-126

headlines.description: — Caleb Martin had a season-high 24 points and a career-best 12 rebounds, Duncan Robinson scored 10 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter and the Miami Heat beat the Toronto Raptors 112-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Martin has season-high 24 points and career-high 12 rebounds as Heat beat Raptors 112-103

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges tied a career high with 45 points on his last trip to Atlanta
headlines.shortLinkText: Mikal Bridges scores 32, including game-winning basket, as Nets beat Hawks 114-113

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 16 points and 21 rebounds and the NBA-leading Minnesota Timberwolves held on to beat San Antonio 102-94 on Wednesday night for their fifth straight victory and the Spurs' 15th loss in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert has 16 points and 21 rebounds, helps Timberwolves beat Wembanyama, Spurs 102-94

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 29 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the short-handed Charlotte Hornets 111-100 on Wednesday for their third straight victory following a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 29 points, Bulls beat short-handed Hornets 111-100

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 23 points and the Houston Rockets snapped a three-game skid with a 110-101 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dillon Brooks scores 23, Rockets snap a 3-game skid with a 110-101 win over Thunder

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 40 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists playing only three periods after the first first-half triple-double of his career in the Dallas Mavericks’ 147-97 victory over the Utah Jazz on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic has first first-half triple-double in Mavericks' 147-97 victory over Jazz

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga finally checked into the game for the first time with 4:45 left in the third quarter. He hadn’t even been in coach Steve Kerr’s pregame plans against Portland, not expected to be part of the rotation given how hard it is for Kerr...
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 31 points, Warriors rally to beat Trail Blazers 110-106

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers are starting to figure out who they are since James Harden's arrival a month ago.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers overcome Jokic's triple-double to beat Nuggets 111-102 and snap 8-game skid against champs
